Citation.sTitle: Excess Gibbs energies of binary mixtures formed by nitrobenzene with selected compounds at 94.95 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Bubble point temperatures (at 94.95 kPa) over the entire composition range are measured for the binary mixtures formed by nitrobenzne with: bromobenzene, N,N-dimethyl formamaide, o-, m- and p-cresols, employing a Swietoslawski type ebulliometer.Wilson equation is used to represent the measured liquid phase composition versus bubble temperature data and the computed values of the excess Gibbs energy are tabulated and discussed.
